name: David Griffiths
talk: From Local State to Global Control: A Journey through React State Management
description:
He has been writing software since he was about 12 years old, and although some of his early code wasn't top-notch, it's safe to assume you've never come across it.

Since then, he has gone through the ups and downs of puberty, an experience he prefers not to delve into. He pursued higher education and took on various jobs that primarily involved typing and coding.

He has authored several books, including notable works on Android development In addition to his writing accomplishments, he offers courses on the reputable O'Reilly Media learning platform  One of his noteworthy courses is "The Agile Sketchpad," an illustrated resource that provides valuable insights into the world of agile software development projects. If you're interested, Apart from his literary and educational pursuits, he is the founder of a company specializing in a cloud-based version of traditional clocking-in and clocking-out machines streamlines attendance management and offers development consultancy services for Android and front-end web development.

name: Antonio Melé
talk: Practical Django: Building a developer stats app using Django and the Github API
description:
Author of Django by Example, a Python web development book with 4 editions published in 8 languages, including a Simplified Chinese edition published by Tsinghua University Press, and other editions published in English, Spanish, Brazilian Portuguese, Korean, Russian, Polish and Serbo-Croatian. 
 CTO and Co-Founder of Nucoro, the wealtech platform for financial institutions (Acquired by Backbase). Former CTO of Exo Investing, the digital wealth management using Artificial Intelligence. 
 Passionate about improving people’s lives through technology. Focused on building and scaling digital financial products and technical teams.
